simple-motd (1.2.6-1) stable; urgency=low

  * Changed method of determining the user in /etc/profile.d/simple-motd
    to use the whoami command to fix the user being incorrect in
    certain circumstances.

  * Revised version numbers to remove "~mf" as original source on
    github has not been updated since 2019.

  * Removed build dependency on dh-exec. Removed dh-exec from install
    file as it was not being used.

  * Compressed manual entry.

  * Corrected the depreciated usage of "=" for ">=" in debian/control.

  * Removed shlib:depends from debian/control as it was not being
    used.

  * Changed source format to 3.0 (quilt).

  * Changed manpage description to a single line only to remove lintian
    warning about the NAME field.

  * Removed comments from debian/rules to clear lintian boilerplate
    warning.

  * Revamped Old prompts to user during installation to use Debconf
    along with po for translations that presents the user with the
    option to specify a user to use with Simple-MOTD or to display
    to all users.
    - Re-Wrote postinst and postrm scripts to achieve this.

  * Completed Lintian Check on package. Package now 100% Lintian
    clean with no overrides!

 -- Mark <mark9000@fastmail.org>  Wed, 05 Nov 2025 17:24:19 +0100

